article.headline: Boston College 84, Wichita State 81
article.story: CHARLOTTE AMALIE, U.S. Virgin Islands (AP) -- Craig Smith had 28 points and 13 rebounds for Boston College, which beat Wichita State 84-81 Monday night to win the Paradise Jam tournament title. Jermaine Watson added 17 points and Jared Dudley 14. Watson was 11-for-12 from the free-throw line for Boston College (3-0), and scored the final eight points on foul shots. Fridge Holman missed a potential game-tying 3-pointer as time expired. Rob Kampman had 21 points for Wichita State (2-1). Jamar Howard added 19 points, and Randy Burns and Bret Wise 10 apiece for the Shockers. The Eagles build an 11-point lead midway through the first half. But the Shockers had a 20-11 surge and trailed 41-39 at the break.
